===Etymology===
From Latin {{term|rhetorica|rhētorica|langg=la}} < {{etyl|grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ῥητορική|tr=rētorikē|lang=grc}}, feminine form of {{term|sc=polytonic|ῥητορικός|tr=rētorikos||concerning public speech|lang=grc}} < {{term|sc=polytonic|ῥήτωρ|tr=rētōr||public speaker|lang=grc}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# The [[art]] of using [[language]], especially public speaking, as a means to [[persuade]].
# [[meaningless|Meaningless]] [[language]] with an exaggerated style [[intend]]ed to [[impress]].
#: ''It's only so much '''rhetoric'''.''

